definition.value: This is an AE which is a benign tumor of striated muscle.
This is an AE which is a bacterial infection of the skeletal muscles which results in an abscess.
This is an AE which is a disease of the muscle  in which the muscle fibers do not function properly.
This is an AE which is a tough, high-tensile-strength band of dense fibrous connective tissue that connects muscle to bone and feel it discomfortable.
This is an AE which is a painful shoulder disorder characterised by either single or multiple deposits in the rotator cuff tendon.
This is an AE which is a form of tendon  cell injury which results in the premature death of cells in living tissue by autolysis.
This is an AE which is a permanent shortening of a tendinous muscle or joint.
This is an AE which is a tough, high-tensile-strength band of dense fibrous connective tissue that connects muscle to bone and feel it pain.
This is an AE which is a sudden involuntary contraction of myofascial tissue.
This is an AE which is a syndrome characterized by chronic pain in multiple myofascial trigger points ("knots") and fascial (connective tissue) constrictions.

This is an AE which main cause of the disease is aseptic inflammation of local muscles and connective tissues such as myofascial, which can be manifested as paralysis, distension, and other discomfort, local muscle stiffness, spasm or palpable strain-like nodules.
This is an AE which is a type of muscular dystrophy, a group of genetic disorders that cause progressive muscle loss and weakness.
This is an AE which is the medical term for intercostal muscle pain.
This is an AE which is progressive wasting of muscle tissues.
This is an AE which is an involuntary, spontaneous, localized quivering of a few muscles, or bundles within a muscle, but which are insufficient to move a joint.

This is an AE which occurs in individuals of all ages who are affected by dystonia, a movement disorder in which sustained involuntary muscle contractions cause twisting and repetitive motions or painful and abnormal postures or positions.
This is an AE which is a disorder of  the continuous and passive partial contraction of the muscles, or the muscle's resistance to passive stretch during resting state.
This is an AE which is a brief, involuntary, irregular (lacking rhythm) twitching (different from clonus, which is rhythmic/ regular) of a muscle or a group of muscles.
This is an AE which refers to a family of epilepsies that present with myoclonus.

This is an AE which is a benign, soft tissue tumor composed of myofibroblasts (i.e. immature cells that contain features of myocytes and fibroblasts) that typically occurs in subcutaneous tissue (i.e. lowermost layer of the skin), fascia (i.e. band of connective tissue just beneath the skin), and/or muscles.
This is an AE which is a skin disease that presents with painful, red, raised, and warm patches of skin.
This is an AE which is an inflammatory disease that affects the fascia, other connective tissues, surrounding muscles, blood vessels and nerves.
This is an AE which is an infectious and sometimes fatal viral disease that affects cloven-hoofed animals, including domestic and wild bovids.

This is an AE which is primarily a disorder of healthy children and young adults, characterized by lesions that are primarily painful, subcutaneous nodules on the plantar surface, resembling erythema nodosum.
This is an AE which is a disorder of the plantar fascia, which is the connective tissue which supports the arch of the foot.
This is an AE which is a common skin infection of the feet caused by fungus.
This is an AE which is an abnormal narrowing of the spinal canal or neural foramen that results in pressure on the spinal cord or nerve roots.
This is an AE which is an abnormal narrowing in a blood vessel or other tubular organ or structure such as vertebral foraminal .
This is an AE which is a defect or stress fracture in the pars interarticularis of the vertebral arch.
This is an AE which is an abnormal narrowing in a blood vessel or other tubular organ or structure such as vertebral lateral recess.

This is an AE which is a dislocation of an irregular bone with a complex structure composed of bone and some hyaline cartilage, the proportions of which vary according to the segment of the backbone and the species of vertebrate.
This is an AE which refers to any clinical syndrome with either an excess of movement or a paucity of voluntary and involuntary movements, unrelated to weakness or spasticity.
This is an AE which is the absence of, or a violation of, symmetry  such as limb asymmetry.
This is an AE which is congenital musculoskeletal disorders which primarily affect the upper and lower limbs.
This is an AE which is a physical anomaly that is deleterious, i.e. a structural defect perceived as a problem such as limb malformation.
This is an AE which is a mass on  appendage of a human .
This is an AE which is a rare condition and should be considered a rare differential diagnosis to unexplained back pain.
This is an AE which is a medical condition in which the spinal canal narrows and compresses the nerves and blood vessels at the level of the lumbar vertebrae.
This is an AE which is the displacement of one spinal vertebra compared to another.
This is an AE which is flattening of the five vertebrae between the rib cage and the pelvis.
This is an AE which is a syndrome in which the facet joints (synovial diarthroses, from L2 to S1) cause painful symptoms.
This is an AE which is a disorder of the hand that can be congenital or acquired.
This is an AE which in older people is common following treatment for a wrist fracture, particularly after non-surgical treatment.
This is an AE which presents with hyperkeratotic, fissure-prone, erythematous areas of the middle or proximal palm, and the volar surfaces of the fingers may also be involved.
This is an AE which is a fungal infection of the hand, mostly a type of dermatophytosis, often part of two feet-one hand syndrome.
This is an AE which is a common infection caused by a group of enteroviruses.
This is an AE which is a symptom characterized by slow, involuntary, convoluted, writhing movements of the fingers, hands, toes, and feet and in some cases, arms, legs, neck and tongue.
This is an AE which is a small benign tumor that forms primarily in areas where the skin forms creases (or rubs together), such as the neck, armpit and groin.
This is an AE which is a heritable connective tissue disorder that affects joints and ligaments.
This is an AE which is medical conditions affecting soft tissue.
